            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I think I found a better solution. It appears that the value of `$fish_user_paths` is prepended to the PATH in each new shell, so I deleted that universal variable and set it to a global variable from my config.fish:\r\n\r\n```fish\r\nif status is-login\r\n\tfish_add_path --global \\\r\n\t\t~/.local/bin \\\r\n\t\t$GOPATH/bin \\\r\n\t\t/opt/homebrew/bin \\\r\n\t\t/opt/homebrew/sbin \\\r\n\t\t/opt/homebrew/opt/fzf/bin\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis works for me in that mason.nvim can still add its bin directory to the PATH in `:terminal` _and_ directories added by direnv don't get bumped to the middle of the list.\r\n\r\nThere seems to be a proposal to get rid of universal variables in fish anyway:\r\nhttps://github.com/fish-shell/fish-shell/issues/7379",
